    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-01-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-01-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="364"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Lord Lyons</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-01-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 17, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I beg to offer you my thanks for your note of the
                    day before yesterday’s date, and for the translation, which you were so good as
                    to send with it, of a communication, dated the 8th instant, which you had
                    received from Mr. Tassara, concerning the affair of the Blanche.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, &amp;c.,
                    &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>LYONS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
